title: Zucman tax: 'The super-rich pay significantly fewer taxes than their fellow citizens, and yet extreme wealth is almost always tied to business'
subhed: Former MPs Gilles Carrez (Les Républicains, right-wing) and Valérie Rabault (Parti Socialiste, left-wing) share a desire for fiscal fairness, but in this op-ed for Le Monde, they highlight the issue of funds from accumulated, undistributed dividends that, after corporate tax is paid, escape all personal taxation.

title: In Greece, an abbot is arrested for trafficking religious artifacts
subhed: Affiliated with the monastery of Kalavryta, in the Peloponnese, the clergyman was caught as he attempted to sell 14 Byzantine icons and two 18th-century Gospels for the sum of €200,000.

title: Charlie Kirk's memorial through the lens of photographer Stacy Kranitz: 'The first few hours felt like a megachurch service'
subhed: Stacy Kranitz, an American photographer born in 1974, covered the memorial ceremony for the ultraconservative activist on September 21 for Le Monde. She reflects on this spectacular event, which combined politics with religion.

title: Samson of Gaza and Samson of Ukraine

subhed: Nicolas Sarkozy will become the first former president of the French Republic to sleep behind bars after being convicted of criminal conspiracy, in the case of alleged Libyan financing of his 2007 presidential campaign.

title: Svalbard, the fastest-warming place on Earth
subhed: 'Our planet at +1.5°C' (1/6). The Norwegian archipelago has warmed by 4°C over the past 30 years. Landslides and thawing permafrost threaten the population, whose way of life is highly greenhouse gas-intensive.
